<para> The Single-Tier ODBC Drivers for <ulink url="MySQL">MySQL</ulink>  conform to the common architectural perceptions of an ODBC driver -- a single component installed on a desktop, workstation, or application server machine.</para><para>The <ulink url="OpenLink">OpenLink</ulink>  Single-Tier Drivers for <ulink url="MySQL">MySQL</ulink>  are a Type B class of driver developed using the <ulink url="MySQL">MySQL</ulink>  network (wire) protocol interface eliminating the need for the installation of any <ulink url="MySQL">MySQL</ulink>  specific client networking software.</para><para>The drivers are currently available for <ulink url="MySQL">MySQL</ulink>  versions 3.x, 4.x and beyond.</para><para>  [[/images/aodbcst.gif|]]</para><para> /<ulink url="MySQL">MySQL</ulink> Single-Tier Architecture Diagram Image scaled down; Click to enlarge./</para><para> This driver is available for Windows, Linux, Unix(most popular flavours), and Mac OS X Operating systems.</para><para> </para></section></docbook>